; dash.tres — the defensive verb (the Hades dash, studied frame-for-frame).
;
; Design intent: this is the second half of the skill ceiling. A directional double-tap
; (or Shift) blinks the player ~205px with i-frames. It cancels the recovery of ANY action
; (it's in every action's cancel_into list), so a skilled player uses it to:
;   - escape melee_heavy's 24f recovery instead of eating the punish
;   - phase through a telegraphed sniper shot
;   - reposition behind a shielded enemy (the front-armor counter)
; A masher doesn't dash intentionally and eats the recovery/punish.
;
; Long cooldown (60f = 1s) so it can't be spammed — each dash is a committed decision.
;
[gd_resource type="Resource" script_class="ActionDef" load_steps=2 format=3]

[ext_resource type="Script" path="res://src/sim/ActionDef.gd" id="1_ad"]

